[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/new_minor_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{With 12 points you know game is likely, but for now you bid 1\H. Partner rebids 1NT. What do you say next? 

Partner has 12-14 points, balanced. If he is at the top, game could still be there, but you aren't sure where to play. If partner has only 2 \Hs then NT is probably best, but if he has 3 \Hs then you would prefer to play the 8-card Major fit. New Minor Forcing will allow partner to answer both questions for you. So you bid 2\C. Partner answers with 2NT.  

Partner tells you he has only 2 \Hs. He also tells you he only has 12-13 points. So you pass 2NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "W:K43.K92.J85.AK86 Q982.54.K973.942 A7.AQT63.QT4.753 JT65.J87.A62.QJT"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
1C pass 1H pass 1NT pass 2D pass 3H pass 4H all pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "17486b9f8879fe94005ef75de4521a4d5c1430f76cb8665cdf06bf13a4f250ef"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/new_minor_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{With 14 points you open your 4-card minor, 1\C. Partner responds 1\H.  

This is easy. You cannot support \Hs at this point with only 3 cards. So you rebid 1NT.

Partner says 2\D.  

This is New Minor Forcing. Partner wants to know if you have 3 \Hs. Not only do you have 3 good \Hs, but you also have a maximum hand. So you jump to 3\H and partner bids the game.}

